html recommendation: 
    not case sensitive : but to use lowercase
    don't require quote : but recommended , width = " 30px", 
    In some situations, when the attribute value itself contains double quotes, it is necessary to use single quotes:
    title = 'the "rajesh" star'

tag, element, empty element, attributes, 

element : opening tag + content + closing tag
attributes : it provide additional information about HTML elements.
    ex : src, href, style , alt , height, width




Inline elements :
elements that do not start on a new line and only take up as much width as necessary.
ex: span, a , strong, em, img, input, br, i , b

Block level ements:
HTML elements that typically start on a new line and occupy the full width available 
ex : div, p, h1, ul, ol, form, table (tr, th,td in table context only)


Global attributes : Attributes that can be applied to any HTML element, regardless of its type. 
    ex: class, id, style, title, lang, dir, accesskey, contenteditable

iframe tag  is used to display a web page within a web page.

semantics : header , footer, section

html vs xml

<p title="topic name "> when we add a title to  paragraph , its called tooltip </p>
